      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>As a move action, a kaa-leki can attempt a @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.GMkLZsN3a7YPvA03.JournalEntryPage.gZlg2ZKze0erNLmP]{Perception} check against a construct it can see (DC = 15 + 1-1/2 × the construct’s CR). On a success, the kaa-leki’s next successful attack against that construct made before the end of their next turn deals an additional amount of damage equal to twice their Wisdom modifier; this extra damage bypasses all DR.</p>\n<p><em>When using this ability, if target construct has DR, extra damage that bypasses DR must be manually accounted for. The system does not provide a means for this extra damage to ignore DR.</em></p>"
